commit.message:
Fix build for NetBSD (and presumably DragonFly BSD)

These both use POSIX threads. I got a link error when cross-compiling
using Nixpkgs (Linux -> NetBSD) that went away once I passed `-pthread`.

The autoconf is crafted to have the same conditional as the C code itself.

verification.payload:
tree f229b092a3748a638ffc55641ba4f35c323e8424
parent f1c96e13727b99925acff76d3e95a7c86414dde8
author John Ericson <John.Ericson@Obsidian.Systems> 1684472247 -0400
committer The Tumultuous Unicorn Of Darkness <the-tumultuous-unicorn-of-darkness@gmx.com> 1695480921 +0200

Fix build for NetBSD (and presumably DragonFly BSD)

These both use POSIX threads. I got a link error when cross-compiling
using Nixpkgs (Linux -> NetBSD) that went away once I passed `-pthread`.

The autoconf is crafted to have the same conditional as the C code itself.
